        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p>The NMJ Anniversary Guide</p>",
        "description": "<p>Anniversaries are a way of returning, year after year, to the day everything shifted. Some are marked with paper, cotton, flowers or wood; others with silver, pearl, ruby, gold or diamond. Each tradition offers a small language of its own – a way to give shape to time, and to honour the love that has gathered there.</p><p>This guide brings together traditional anniversary gifts, modern interpretations and the gemstones or metals often associated with each year. Think of it not as a rulebook, but as a place to begin – a prompt for choosing gifts with meaning and memory.</p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
    "22942553-01da-4697-89ac-f500b502883f": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "template--16177341137065__22942553-01da-4697-89ac-f500b502883f-image-3": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>1ST ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Paper<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Clocks<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Gold</p><p>The first year is still so close to the beginning, and paper feels fitting: a page, a letter, a photograph, the first chapter still being written. Clocks offer a reminder of the time you are now building together, while gold brings warmth and permanence to this earliest milestone.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>5TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Wood<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silverware<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>Wood is about roots, and five years in, a marriage has usually found some of its foundations. Sapphire, long associated with loyalty and sincerity, brings a steadiness to this anniversary.<br/><br/><br/><strong>10th ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Tin or Aluminium<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond Jewellery<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Diamond</p><p>Ten years deserves something with a little brilliance, and while tin and aluminium may seem like humble materials, they’re flexible, useful and enduring – qualities any long love knows well. Diamond brings the ceremony of the milestone into focus: a decade of choosing each other, and a future still opening up ahead.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>1ST ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Paper<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Clocks<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Gold</p><p>The first year is still so close to the beginning, and paper feels fitting: a page, a letter, a photograph, the first chapter still being written. Clocks offer a reminder of the time you are now building together, while gold brings warmth and permanence to this earliest milestone.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>5TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Wood<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silverware<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>Wood is about roots, and five years in, a marriage has usually found some of its foundations. Sapphire, long associated with loyalty and sincerity, brings a steadiness to this anniversary.<br/><br/><br/><strong>10th ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Tin or Aluminium<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond Jewellery<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Diamond</p><p>Ten years deserves something with a little brilliance, and while tin and aluminium may seem like humble materials, they’re flexible, useful and enduring – qualities any long love knows well. Diamond brings the ceremony of the milestone into focus: a decade of choosing each other, and a future still opening up ahead.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
