    "content_list_anbznK": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_tAWrNQ": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>15TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Crystal<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Watch<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Ruby</p><p>Crystal catches the light differently from every angle, much like a life shared over many years. At 15 years there is history and a deeper kind of seeing. A watch marks the time passed, while ruby evokes a love still burning brightly.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>20TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> China<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Platinum<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>China is delicate, but enduring when cared for. And there’s something lovely in that to mark 20 years: the idea that precious things are made to be used, and held and looked after. Platinum represents strength and rarity, while emerald carries the feeling of renewal – proof that love can keep growing, even after so much time.<br/><br/><br/><strong>25TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Silver<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silver<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Silver</p><p>Silver marks 25 years with classic elegance. It’s luminous without being loud, and precious without needing to be coddled. A silver anniversary is a beautiful pause: a chance to look back at the years gathered behind you, and to recognise the grace of all that has held.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>1ST ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Paper<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Clocks<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Gold</p><p>The first year is still so close to the beginning, and paper feels fitting: a page, a letter, a photograph, the first chapter still being written. Clocks offer a reminder of the time you are now building together, while gold brings warmth and permanence to this earliest milestone.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>5TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Wood<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silverware<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>Wood is about roots, and five years in, a marriage has usually found some of its foundations. Sapphire, long associated with loyalty and sincerity, brings a steadiness to this anniversary.<br/><br/><br/><strong>10th ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Tin or Aluminium<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond Jewellery<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Diamond</p><p>Ten years deserves something with a little brilliance, and while tin and aluminium may seem like humble materials, they’re flexible, useful and enduring – qualities any long love knows well. Diamond brings the ceremony of the milestone into focus: a decade of choosing each other, and a future still opening up ahead.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
