    "content_list_wQQnew": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_MyRJ63": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>30TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Pearl<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Pearl</p><p>Pearl returns at 30 years and it feels especially right here. Layer by layer, over time, something luminous is formed – it’s not perfect in spite of that process, but because of it. Diamonds add brightness to the milestone, but pearls give it soul: patient and intimate.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>35TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Coral<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Jade<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>Coral, jade and emerald each bring their own sense of life to the 35th year. There is colour and vitality, and the feeling of something still <em>moving</em>. This is a milestone for a love that has not stood still, but continued to deepen and find new forms.<br/><br/><br/><strong>40TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Ruby<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Ruby<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Ruby</p><p>Ruby is all heart. Deep red, vivid and unmistakable, it has long been tied to passion, courage and devotion. After 40 years, it feels less like a symbol of new romance and more like a tribute to love that has kept its warmth through time, change, family, memory and everything in between.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>1ST ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Paper<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Clocks<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Gold</p><p>The first year is still so close to the beginning, and paper feels fitting: a page, a letter, a photograph, the first chapter still being written. Clocks offer a reminder of the time you are now building together, while gold brings warmth and permanence to this earliest milestone.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>5TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Wood<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silverware<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>Wood is about roots, and five years in, a marriage has usually found some of its foundations. Sapphire, long associated with loyalty and sincerity, brings a steadiness to this anniversary.<br/><br/><br/><strong>10th ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Tin or Aluminium<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond Jewellery<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Diamond</p><p>Ten years deserves something with a little brilliance, and while tin and aluminium may seem like humble materials, they’re flexible, useful and enduring – qualities any long love knows well. Diamond brings the ceremony of the milestone into focus: a decade of choosing each other, and a future still opening up ahead.</p>",
